The course provides an overview of the main principles behind writing a scholarly literature review and formulating one's publishing strategies. After getting acquainted with relevant research literature, the participants of the course will compile their strategies for  publishing peer-reviewed academic articles and present and discuss these at the final seminar of the course.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to develop students skills in analysing academic literature and in planning publishing their research findings.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After taking the course the doctoral student:  -	is well aquainted with the academic literature relevant to their thesis project;  -	is able to identify research gaps and pose research questions;  -	is able to plan one's academic publishing strategies accordingly.
